# Development and Guidelines

## Getting Started
1. Ensure you have Node.js installed (version specified in `.nvmrc`)
2. Install pnpm if not already installed
3. Run `pnpm install` to install dependencies
4. Use `pnpm dev` to start development servers

## Code Style and Quality
- Biome is used for linting and formatting
- Run `pnpm format` to format code
- Run `pnpm lint` to check for issues
- Follow TypeScript best practices
- Write meaningful commit messages

## Package Management
- Use pnpm for all package management
- Add new dependencies using `pnpm add`
- Add dev dependencies using `pnpm add -D`
- Keep dependencies up to date using Renovate

## Git Workflow
- Use conventional commits
- Follow the branching strategy defined in `.github/`
- Run pre-commit hooks (managed by Husky)
- Keep PRs focused and well-documented

## Testing
- Write tests for new features
- Run tests using `pnpm test`
- Maintain good test coverage

## Documentation
- Keep README files up to date
- Document new features and changes
- Update API documentation when needed
- Follow the documentation style guide

## Deployment
- Follow the deployment checklist
- Test in staging before production
- Monitor application after deployment

